Australian Bank Credit Rose 0.3% in January From Prior Month

-- B y   M i c h a e l   H e a t h
-- 
2011-02-28T00:32:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/australian-bank-credit-rose-0-3-in-january-from-prior-month.html
Loans provided by Australian banks
and finance companies increased 0.3 percent in January from the
previous month, the  Reserve Bank  of Australia said today.  The median estimate of 20 economists surveyed by Bloomberg
News was for a 0.3 percent increase. Lending gained 3.3 percent
from a year earlier, the central bank said.  Loans to consumers to buy houses rose 0.6 percent from
December and advanced 7.3 percent from a year earlier, according
to todayâ€™s statement. Credit provided to consumers for purchases
other than housing was flat from a month earlier for an annual
rise of 0.9 percent.  Lending to companies dropped 0.1 percent from December and
declined 2.4 percent from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter for this story:  Michael Heath  in Sydney at 
